This paper discusses a new graphical password scheme that is resistant to shoulder surfing. The paper focuses on the usability of the scheme for PDAs, which suggests a human-computer interaction (HCI) aspect, making cs.HC a likely category. The paper also discusses the security aspects of the scheme, which suggests a computer security (cs.CR) aspect. The use of mnemonics for sequence retrieval suggests a potential category of cybernetics (cs.CY). The paper also discusses the use of complementary measures such as displaying degraded images, which suggests a category of signal processing (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of drawing input, which suggests a category of information theory (cs.IT).
